# heron — Environment Variables (template)
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# ── CRITICAL: where credentials belong ────────────────────────────────────
#
# Heron splits its environment into TWO layers:
#
#   1. .env — MACHINE-WIDE INFRASTRUCTURE. Cookie-signing secret,
#      dashboard origin, OAuth-app credentials, data-dir override, etc.
#      Same value for every user on this install.
#
#   2. Per-user encrypted secrets — PERSONAL credentials (Anthropic /
#      Gemini / Adzuna / Gmail-IMAP keys). Each user manages their own
#      via Settings → API Keys. Stored encrypted at
#      data/users/{uid}/profiles/_shared/secrets.json. See AGENTS.md.
#
# The keys in section "Personal credentials (per-user)" below STILL WORK
# in .env as a single-user fallback — but Heron now prefers the per-user
# store. On first boot after upgrade, install-wide .env values are
# silently copied into the OWNER's encrypted per-user store; .env still
# works as fallback until the maintainer deletes the lines. To migrate:
#
#   1. Sign in as OWNER → Settings → API Keys → verify the masked values
#   2. Delete the corresponding lines from .env
#   3. Other users: sign in → Settings → API Keys → enter their own
#
# Validation: this file is linted by dotenv-linter on every commit
# (see lefthook.yml :: dotenv-lint). Run manually with:
#   pnpm validate:dotenv

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Personal credentials (per-user — Settings UI preferred)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# These keys WORK in .env as a single-user fallback, but the preferred
# location is each user's per-user encrypted store. After first sign-in,
# managed via Settings → API Keys (in the dashboard).

# ── Anthropic (REQUIRED) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Powers Claude — used for deep job evaluations, agent chat, mock interviews,
# interview prep, negotiation drafts, CV-tailoring, cover letters, and the
# plain-text → markdown CV converter in onboarding.
# Get a key: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key_here

# ── Gemini (RECOMMENDED) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for: node gemini-eval.mjs "JD text here"
# Free API key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Free tier: 15 RPM / 1M tokens/day with gemini-2.0-flash (no billing needed)
# Used for first-pass scoring on the daily ~30 new postings before deeper
# Claude evaluation — keeps API costs low.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# Optional: override the default Gemini model
# Default: gemini-2.0-flash (free tier, fast)
# Alternatives: gemini-1.5-flash, gemini-1.5-pro, gemini-2.0-flash-thinking-exp
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash

# ── Adzuna (OPTIONAL) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Adds Adzuna to the JobSpy aggregator list. Skip unless you specifically
# want Adzuna's coverage. Sign up: https://developer.adzuna.com
# ADZUNA_APP_ID=your_app_id
# ADZUNA_APP_KEY=your_app_key

# ── Gmail IMAP (OPTIONAL) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Real-time job-alert ingestion. Polls a Gmail label every 30 min via IMAP
# and parses LinkedIn / Indeed / generic alert emails into the pipeline.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Enable 2-factor auth on your Google account
#   2. Generate an app password at https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#      (pick "Mail" + "Other (custom name)" → "heron")
#   3. Optional: in Gmail create a filter that auto-applies a label to
#      LinkedIn/Indeed alert emails (e.g. "heron/job-alerts"), then
#      point GMAIL_IMAP_LABEL at that label instead of INBOX
#   4. Or use the /sources page (or onboarding "Sources" step) to set
#      these up via UI — credentials are written here automatically
#
# GMAIL_IMAP_HOST=imap.gmail.com
# GMAIL_IMAP_USER=you@gmail.com
# GMAIL_IMAP_PASSWORD=xxxx_xxxx_xxxx_xxxx
# GMAIL_IMAP_LABEL=INBOX

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Machine-wide infrastructure (.env is the ONLY location for these)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# These keys are the same for every user on this install — they secure
# the shared dashboard process or address shared resources. Cannot live
# in the per-user store.

# ── Authentication (multi-user) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Heron supports multiple users on ONE local install — e.g. a couple
# sharing a Mac, or a small team on a homelab. Every job, profile, and
# report is scoped to its owner's user_id.
#
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET — 32+ random hex chars. The app generates this
# automatically on first boot if you don't set it; you only need to set
# it manually if you want predictable cookies across reinstalls.
#   Generate one yourself:  openssl rand -hex 32
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=replace_with_64_hex_chars
#
# BETTER_AUTH_URL — origin the auth callbacks come back to. Defaults to
# http://localhost:5173 (the dev port). Set this only if you're hosting
# the dashboard somewhere other than localhost.
# BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:5173
#
# GitHub OAuth (OPTIONAL) — adds a "Sign in with GitHub" button to the
# login page. Create an OAuth app at https://github.com/settings/developers
# with Authorization callback URL: {BETTER_AUTH_URL}/api/auth/callback/github
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_oauth_client_id
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_oauth_client_secret

# ── Other integrations (add your own below) ──────────────────────────────
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key_here          # Future OpenAI integration

# ── Advanced — overrides (rarely needed) ─────────────────────────────────
# Most users never set these. They exist for cross-machine setups, forks,
# air-gapped installs, and multi-user CLI scripting. Defaults are sensible.
#
# HERON_DATA_DIR — relocate the local data directory (default: ./data).
# Useful if you want heron state on an external drive or a different
# partition. Path is absolute; the directory must already exist.
# HERON_DATA_DIR=/path/to/data
#
# HERON_USER_ID — bypass the "active user" lookup for CLI scripts /
# headless automation (Python apply-*, MJS scan-*). The dashboard always
# uses the logged-in user; this only affects standalone scripts.
# HERON_USER_ID=<uuid-from-data/profiles.json>
#
# HERON_DASHBOARD_URL — used by side scripts (e.g. scan-email-imap)
# that POST results back to the dashboard from a different host on the
# same network. Default: http://127.0.0.1:5174
# HERON_DASHBOARD_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5174
#
# HERON_UPDATE_REPO / _VERSION_URL / _RELEASES_API — override the
# auto-updater's targets. Set if you're tracking a different fork or
# running an air-gapped mirror. Defaults point at the official fork.
# HERON_UPDATE_REPO=https://github.com/your-fork/heron.git
# HERON_UPDATE_VERSION_URL=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-fork/heron/main/VERSION
# HERON_UPDATE_RELEASES_API=https://api.github.com/repos/your-fork/heron/releases/latest
